Summary: a long narrow form with 2 rows of flashing lights
divs: Sighting Detailsmyself and michael were camping in the castleraegh river bed (it was dry).theobject was cigar shaped, a row of slow flashing large white lights on top(maybe6)and smaller coloured ones of varying colour flashing intermittently.It movedroughly zig zag towards us and stopped maybe 200m. away then lifted accross ourpath(maybe 60deg)to about 12 oclock then shot almost straight out until itdisappeared.when it lifted it would have moved at incredible speed.
